cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a video denoising algorithm based on a convolutional neural network architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the performance and computational load of the algorithm, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the ability to handle a wide range of noise levels, which could suggest information theory (cs.IT) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks in the algorithm could also place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
